about.aboutContent:
DVRPC Bicycle Network Inventory


DVRPC is seeking the help of local planning partners to keep our region’s bicycle network inventory up to date. This data is used in a variety of analytic contexts, including DVRPC’s Level of Traffic Stress (LTS) and regional travel demand models. Furthermore, the outputs of these analyses are used to shape our region. As a result, this map exists to ensure that DVRPC is aware of new facilities as they are constructed.


Please use this map to inform DVRPC of new on- or off-street bicycle facilities missing from the data. In addition, this map can collect data on existing features that might be inaccurate. Planned projects that are funded and scheduled for implementation are also welcome here, using the “Status” dropdown and an estimated implementation date. If necessary, feel free to use the “Notes” field to provide additional details about the design, limits, or implementation timeline.


If you have any questions, please contact Aaron Fraint (Associate Manager, DVRPC Office of Mobility Analysis and Design)


The video below demonstrates the usage of this map. It can also be found by clicking the “?” icon on the map.
